channel.title: I'm back! (do you like where RSPS' are heading?)
channel.description: Well after a good while of being away from the forums to finish Highschool. . .I am back to see how RSPS have changed. Do you guys like where these servers are headed? Personally I don't. . .I am an old school RSPS player, but I want to hear what you guys like!

item.title: I'm back! (do you like where RSPS' are heading?)
item.dc:creator: @Christmas_tree Christmas_tree
item.description:
@Christmas_tree wrote:

R A R E S:

Well after a good while of being away from the forums to finish Highschool. . .I am back to see how RSPS have changed. Do you guys like where these servers are headed? Personally I don’t. . .I am an old school RSPS player, but I want to hear what you guys like!

Welcome back, even though I’ve never heard of you. RSPS’s are and always have been a crappy mess. The only reason people like me hang around is to help others and to compliment the beautiful structure of the 317 protocol, and cuss and swear about how poorly implemented it is within a standard winterLove story.

RSPS now has one direction, and that’s to perfectly emulate 2006-8 periods. New runescape servers from '07 will soon kill this idea off, and it won’t be long before we see surges in custom servers with ::item such as frugooscape used to be

tl;dr - I stay to jaba
